 {"id":"sqlmodel_rust-b0q.1","title":"Postgres: Implement message framing and parsing","description":"# Task: Implement PostgreSQL Message Framing and Parsing

## Context
PostgreSQL uses a simple message format with a type byte and length prefix. This task implements the foundational message encoding/decoding layer.

## Message Format

### Standard Message (after startup)
```
+------+--------+------------------+
| Type | Length | Payload          |
| 1B   | 4B     | (Length-4) bytes |
+------+--------+------------------+
```

Length includes itself (4 bytes) but not the type byte.

### Startup Message (first message from client)
```
+--------+------------------+
| Length | Payload          |
| 4B     | (Length-4) bytes |
+--------+------------------+
```

No type byte for startup message.

## Message Types

### Frontend Messages (Client -> Server)
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum FrontendMessage {
    /// Startup message (no type byte)
    Startup {
        version: i32,    // 196608 for 3.0
        params: Vec<(String, String)>,
    },

    /// Password response
    PasswordMessage(String),

    /// SASL authentication
    SASLInitialResponse {
        mechanism: String,
        data: Vec<u8>,
    },
    SASLResponse(Vec<u8>),

    /// Simple query
    Query(String),

    /// Extended query protocol
    Parse {
        name: String,      // "" for unnamed
        query: String,
        param_types: Vec<u32>,  // OIDs
    },
    Bind {
        portal: String,
        statement: String,
        param_formats: Vec<i16>,  // 0=text, 1=binary
        params: Vec<Option<Vec<u8>>>,  // None for NULL
        result_formats: Vec<i16>,
    },
    Describe {
        kind: char,  // 'S' for statement, 'P' for portal
        name: String,
    },
    Execute {
        portal: String,
        max_rows: i32,  // 0 for all
    },
    Close {
        kind: char,
        name: String,
    },
    Sync,
    Flush,

    /// Copy operations
    CopyData(Vec<u8>),
    CopyDone,
    CopyFail(String),

    /// Terminate connection
    Terminate,

    /// Cancel request (separate connection)
    CancelRequest {
        process_id: i32,
        secret_key: i32,
    },
}
```

